    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nI followed all the build instructions from the BUILD.md and I have all the required deps.\r\nI haven't changed anything on any of the files after git clone and I even ran and removed the previous nvim version;\r\n```sh\r\nsudo rm -f /usr/local/bin/nvim && sudo rm -rf /usr/local/share/nvim\r\n```\r\n\r\nhowever; after running the final step in the build step: sudo make install\r\nI open nvim only to be greeted by an error message:\r\n\r\n**E484: Can't open file /usr/local/share/nvim/syntax/syntax.vim**\r\n\r\nwhen I run: **echo $VIMRUNTIME**\r\ninside nvim I get: **/usr/local/share/nvim**\r\n\r\nit seems that nvim is looking for **/usr/local/share/nvim/syntax/syntax.vim** but the real path of syntax.vim is: **/usr/local/share/nvim/runtime/syntax/syntax.vim**\r\n\r\nI'm not sure what I did wrong as I followed all the steps as they were in BUILD.md. \r\n\r\nI have already tried to make distclean, delete previous nvim and reinstall nvim and no matter what I do I get the same error after I open nvim.\r\n\r\nIf anybody could please help me or point me in the right direction, I would highly appreciate it.\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n```sh\r\nsudo rm -f /usr/local/bin/nvim && sudo rm -rf /usr/local/share/nvim\r\n```\r\n\r\nThen:\r\n```sh\r\ncd neovim/ && make distclean\r\n```\r\n\r\nAfterwards:\r\n```sh\r\nmake CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=RelWithDebInfo\r\n```\r\nFinally:\r\n```sh\r\nsudo make install\r\n```\r\nIt builds successfully but upon opening nvim:\r\nE484: Can't open file /usr/local/share/nvim/syntax/syntax.vim\r\n\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nnvim opens with no error messages.\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nnvim v0.10.0-dev-2039+g583c1de17\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nno\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nArch Linux x86_64\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nalacritty 0.13.0\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-256color\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nbuilt from source",
