            "body": "> > when I run: echo $VIMRUNTIME\r\n> > inside nvim I get: /usr/local/share/nvim\r\n> \r\n> That is incorrect; it should be `/usr/local/share/nvim/runtime`.\r\n> \r\n> Do you have write permissions on `/usr/local`?\r\n\r\nI do not. I'm on a fresh install of Arch. I thought it was normal to not have write permission to **/usr/local/** as that path should only have read permission? \r\n\r\nAm I wrong? if so, how do I fix it? \r\nThank you for the timely reply.",
