            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Is there any other config in your shell in your nvim config that sets `$VIMRUNTIME`? That's sounds very strange that `$VIMRUNTIME` points to a wrong directory even if you did a clean-install.\r\n\r\nIn your shell, please try:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\nenv | grep VIM\r\n\r\nbash -c 'echo $VIMRUNTIME'\r\n\r\nnvim --clean --headless -c 'echo $VIMRUNTIME' -c 'q'\r\n```\r\n",
