            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "> Is there any other config in your shell in your nvim config that sets `$VIMRUNTIME`? That's sounds very strange that `$VIMRUNTIME` points to a wrong directory even if you did a clean-install.\r\n> \r\n> In your shell, please try:\r\n> \r\n> ```shell\r\n> env | grep VIM\r\n> \r\n> bash -c 'echo $VIMRUNTIME'\r\n> \r\n> nvim --clean --headless -c 'echo $VIMRUNTIME' -c 'q'\r\n> ```\r\n\r\nthank you so much for pointing me in the right direction. It was definetily that. I managed to remove all nvim and did a clean install. Turns out it was my previous config.lua that had incorrectly set the path of VIMRUNTIME, but I'm still not sure why. Problem solved.",
